headline: SHW Q3 Deep Dive: Share Gains and Cost Controls Offset Ongoing Market Weakness
summary: Paint and coating manufacturer Sherwin-Williams (NYSE:SHW) reported Q3 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 3.2% year on year to $6.36 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $5.43 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.59 per share was 4.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
